    <compoundname>helios::engine::mechanics::lifecycle::components::Active</compoundname>
    <briefdescription>
<para>Tag component indicating that an entity is active. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This empty struct serves as a marker component for filtering active entities in views. It is automatically managed by `GameObject::setActive()`.</para>
<para>When `setActive(true)` is called:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>The `Active` tag is added</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>The `Inactive` tag is removed</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>`onActivate()` is called on components that support it</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>## Usage in Views</para>
<para>```cpp // Query only active entities for (auto [entity, health, active] : gameWorld-&gt;view&lt; HealthComponent, <ref refid="structhelios_1_1engine_1_1mechanics_1_1lifecycle_1_1components_1_1Active" kindref="compound">Active</ref> &gt;().whereEnabled()) { // Process only active entities } ```</para>
